## Phase scope

Never exceed the **current phase**. Start at Phase 0 (`10-phase-0-foundation.md`) until acceptance passes, then Phase 1, etc. Phase 2+ features (karigar, schemes, voice, hardware) are out of scope until that phase.

## STOP and ask / escalate

Money math not in plan · new library not in stack · plan contradictions · ambiguous business rule · destructive migration · tenant isolation risk · change spans >5 files / >2 modules · user request contradicts a locked plan · secrets · RLS changes · `packages/domain/billing/*` · staff seeing cost prices · disabling tests · CI workflow changes

## Hard nos

- No JS `number` for money — `Decimal.js` in domain, `NUMERIC` in DB, `string` on wire
- No RLS bypass (except explicit `SECURITY DEFINER` admin aggregates)
- No direct `@radix-ui/*` / `lucide-react` / `cmdk` imports in apps — use `@sonari/ui`
- No new library without ADR · no `.env` commits · no work on `main` · no push to `main`
- No inventing endpoints/tables — implement plan specs or propose via ADR
- Never trust LLM output for money — validate with `packages/domain`

## Stack (locked — ADR-001/002/003)

Vite + React 18 + RR v6 · Fastify · Tailwind · shadcn/ui + IndiaCN · Supabase (Mumbai) · BullMQ + Upstash · Dexie · Cloudflare Pages + Fly.io bom · Turborepo + pnpm

## After task

1. **Plan deviations** table first (or "None — implemented as planned"): what the plan said → what we did → why
2. Plans updated in `Plans/` (+ ADR if non-trivial) — never leave docs stale
3. Files changed, tests run

Never silently diverge. Never claim done while plans are stale or deviations are unreported.
